Croton

are trees, shrubs, subshrubs, herbs or scandent shrubs, usually monoecious, rarely dioecious. The indumentum is mostly composed of stellate or lepidote trichomes. The thyrsoid inflorescences have pistillate flowers in proximal cymules and staminate ones in distal ones. The filaments are inflexed in bud and the petals of the pistillate flowers are reduced, obsolete or absent (

).

